{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"QceJfxoeInxsLwOKqzSFw","title":"Rule 3","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"from":{"fname":"ext.deep-work","id":"GubAN8JRkCVLNRBsX_5e4","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":320},"end":{"line":12,"column":43,"offset":362},"indent":[]},"value":"ext.deep-work.rule-3"},{"from":{"fname":"archive.daily.journal.2021.06.30","id":"TASqHuovDQXuwR7XkwEa6","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":60,"column":1,"offset":3731},"end":{"line":60,"column":25,"offset":3755},"indent":[]},"value":"ext.deep-work.rule-3"}],"anchors":{"rule-3":{"type":"header","value":"rule-3","line":8,"column":0},"the":{"type":"header","value":"the","line":19,"column":0},"the-1":{"type":"header","value":"the-1","line":25,"column":0},"apply-the-law-of-the-vital-few-to-your-internet-habits":{"type":"header","value":"apply-the-law-of-the-vital-few-to-your-internet-habits","line":29,"column":0},"quit-social-media":{"type":"header","value":"quit-social-media","line":34,"column":0},"dont-use-the-internet-to-entertain-yourself":{"type":"header","value":"dont-use-the-internet-to-entertain-yourself","line":40,"column":0}},"fname":"ext.deep-work.rule-3","updated":1624871661769,"created":1624867711880,"parent":"GubAN8JRkCVLNRBsX_5e4","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"041f1474c19d34c48d2b5038719131a3","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"rule-3\">Rule 3<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#rule-3\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"rule-3-1\">Rule #3<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#rule-3-1\"></a></h1>\n<p><em><strong>Quit Social Media</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your willpower is limited.</li>\n<li>Social media feeds your short-circuited brain instant gratification.</li>\n<li>You have less time and energy for deep work.</li>\n<li>These tools are not inherently evil.\n<ul>\n<li>If you can find value in it, feel free to use them.</li>\n<li>But don't operate under the <em>any-benefit</em> mindset.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"the-any-benefit-mindset\">The <em>Any-benefit mindset</em>.<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#the-any-benefit-mindset\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Justifying the use of social media if you can identify <em>any</em> possible benefit from it.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>This ignores the negatives that come with social media.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Throughout history, skilled laborers have meticulously thought about choosing the right tools for them, and knowledge workers should do the same.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"the-craftsman-approach-to-tool-selection\">The <em>Craftsman Approach</em> to tool selection.<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#the-craftsman-approach-to-tool-selection\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify the core factors that determine success.</li>\n<li>Adopt the tool if it increase the likelihood of said success, even after factoring in the negatives that come along with it.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"apply-the-law-of-the-vital-few-to-your-internet-habits\">Apply the Law of the Vital Few to Your Internet Habits<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#apply-the-law-of-the-vital-few-to-your-internet-habits\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>80% of a given effect is due to just 20% of the possible causes.</li>\n<li>a.k.a the Pareto principle, 80/20 rule, principle of factor sparsity.</li>\n<li>If you spend time on the low-impact activities, you are taking away time that could otherwise be spent on high-impact activities.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"quit-social-media\">Quit Social Media<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#quit-social-media\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>You are not really missing out.</li>\n<li>People don't actually <em>want to hear what you have to say</em>.\n<ul>\n<li>Social media is designed to give you an easy way to signal your opinion to others.\n<ul>\n<li>_You \"like\" my status update and I'll \"like\" yours. This agreement gives everyone a simulacrum of importance without requiring much effort in return.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"dont-use-the-internet-to-entertain-yourself\">Don't use the Internet to Entertain Yourself<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#dont-use-the-internet-to-entertain-yourself\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Outside of the 8 hour workday, you have 16 hours all to yourself.</li>\n<li>Treat them like a day within a day, not a prologue or epilogue to your \"work day\".</li>\n<li>Deliberately making use of your day outside the time you work.</li>\n<li>Put more thought into your leisure time.\n<ul>\n<li>Don't default to what grabs your attention at the moment.</li>\n<li>Spend some time thinking what you can do with your time instead.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Some may say adding structure to your leisure time will make you more tired for the next work day, but this is not the case.\n<ul>\n<li>It will <em>increase</em> the value instead.</li>\n<li>What your mind needs is <em>change</em> not <em>rest</em>. They don't get tired like your limbs.\n<ul>\n<li>Except until you do need to rest (e.g. attention fatigue, etc.), which is why we sleep.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>If you give your mind something meaningful, your day will be more fulfilled and be ready to start a new one the next day.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/GubAN8JRkCVLNRBsX_5e4\">Deep Work</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">2021-06-30 (Private)</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"919a3a68-d78d-4403-aca5-ea6e722ca35b","title":"Cerebrarium","desc":"","updated":1640613661592,"created":1608971683570,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"cerebrarium","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"608b5806f5a9617a1356f40276dc6043","links":